<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1322,283,430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,466,283,309]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Discussion.–</emphasis>
This species curiously resembles the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1100,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[992,1100,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Apenesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the texture and appearance of clypeus and head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
